Vice President Mike Pence visited Ramstein Air Base in Germany to meet with members of the United States Air Force and thank them for their service. He delivered a message from President Donald Trump, praising the armed forces as the greatest force for good in the world. Pence also highlighted the administration's efforts to strengthen the military and support its personnel. He announced a successful negotiation with Turkey for a ceasefire in Syria, which would impact missions supported by Ramstein Air Base. Pence expressed gratitude for the sacrifices made by the military and assured them of the support and prayers of the American people.